      def estimator(sample_size):
          a = pd.DataFrame()
          for i in range(0,15):
              a[i] = (2*np.random.random_sample(size = 1000))-1;
          res = (a.apply(abs,axis= 1).apply(np.square,axis = 1).cumsum(axis = 1)**(1/2) <= 1).sum()/1000
          xx = range(15)
          plt.scatter(xx, res, alpha=0.5)
          plt.show()
          return res, print('2-D Estimation of pi is:', res[1]*4, 'and 3-D Estimation of pi is:', res[2]*6 )

      E)
      Here, I add a random noise as described, however since the colour scale is 0-256 in my format, I encountered that values higher than 255 are displayed as white in the image, therefore, I decided to apply modulo function to the formatted pixels so that new values remains in the defined range

      E) Here, I add a random noise as described, however since the colour scale is 0-256 in my format, I encountered that values higher than 255 are displayed as white in the image, therefore, I decided to apply modulo function to the formatted pixels so that new values remains in the defined range

      In [533]:
       
      noisy_image = np.empty((512,512,3))
      for i in range(0,512):
          for j in range(0,512):
              noisy_image[i,j,0] = np.around(image[i,j,0] + 0.1 * np.random.random_sample(size = 1)*image[:,:,0].max())%256
              noisy_image[i,j,1] = np.around(image[i,j,1] + 0.1 * np.random.random_sample(size = 1)*image[:,:,1].max())%256
              noisy_image[i,j,2] = np.around(image[i,j,2] + 0.1 * np.random.random_sample(size = 1)*image[:,:,2].max())%256
